Privacy Policy – GRIDFLOW

Last updated: 7 Feb 2026

1. Introduction

Instinct VR (“the App”) is developed and published by XALT Labs.
This Privacy Policy explains what data the App collects, how it is used, and how users can exercise their rights regarding that data.

2. Data We Collect
Meta Horizon Platform Data

The App uses Meta Horizon platform services to provide core functionality. As a result, the App collects and processes the following data provided by Meta:

Meta User ID – used to identify the logged-in user for platform features

Meta Profile Name – used for in-game display and leaderboards

Meta Profile Image – used for in-game user interface display

Leaderboard and Achievement Data – used to display rankings and unlock achievements

This data is provided directly by Meta when the user logs into the App.

Support Communications

If you contact us for support, we may receive personal information that you voluntarily provide (such as your email address and message content).

3. How We Use Data

The App uses Meta Horizon platform data solely for the following purposes:

Displaying the user’s profile name and profile image within the App

Displaying user names in Meta-managed leaderboards

Unlocking and displaying Meta-managed achievements

Enabling platform authentication and identification

Support communication data is used only to respond to user inquiries.

4. Data Storage and Sharing

The App does not store Meta Horizon User Data on external servers or databases.

All Meta User ID, profile, leaderboard, and achievement data is managed and stored by Meta through its platform services.
The App does not sell, rent, or share personal data with third parties.

5. Data Security

The App does not retain Meta Horizon User Data beyond its use in active application sessions.
Security of platform data is managed by Meta in accordance with its privacy and security practices.

6. User Rights and Data Deletion

Users may manage or delete their Meta Horizon profile data, including User ID, profile name, profile image, leaderboard entries, and achievements, through Meta’s account and privacy settings.

If you have contacted us for support and wish to request deletion of related communications, you may do so by contacting us using the information below.

7. Changes to This Privacy Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be posted with an updated effective date.

8. Contact Us

If you have questions or requests regarding this Privacy Policy, please contact: support@xaltlabs.in
